01:18:35,711 --> 01:18:37,712
was ditching school
and when I was there,

997
01:18:37,797 --> 01:18:39,297
a guy broke into the house.

998
01:18:39,382 --> 01:18:43,093
I called the cops and they picked me up
for making a phony phone call.

999
01:18:43,177 --> 01:18:45,929
What do you care
if your brother ditches school?

1000
01:18:47,056 --> 01:18:50,183
Why should he get to ditch,
when everybody else has to go?

1001
01:18:50,267 --> 01:18:53,853
- You could ditch.
- Yeah, I'd get caught.

1002
01:18:55,314 --> 01:18:56,314
I see.

1003
01:18:57,316 --> 01:19:00,777
So you're pissed off 'cause he ditches
and doesn't get caught, is that it?

1004
01:19:03,906 --> 01:19:05,657
- Basically.
- Basically.

1005
01:19:07,076 --> 01:19:09,327
Then your problem is you.

1006
01:19:09,453 --> 01:19:12,038
- Excuse me?
- Excuse you.

1007
01:19:12,665 --> 01:19:15,250
You ought to spend a little more time
dealing with yourself

1008
01:19:15,334 --> 01:19:18,503
a little less time worrying about
what your brother does.

1009
01:19:18,629 --> 01:19:20,422
That's just an opinion.

1010
01:19:21,132 --> 01:19:23,425
- What are you, a psychiatrist?
- No.

1011
01:19:23,717 --> 01:19:26,094
Then why don't you keep
your opinions to yourself?

1012
01:19:30,307 --> 01:19:32,517
There's somebody you should talk to.

1013
01:19:37,314 --> 01:19:40,567
If you say "Ferris Bueller,"
you lose a testicle.

1014
01:19:41,402 --> 01:19:42,777
Oh, you know him?

1015
01:19:51,704 --> 01:19:54,873
You know, that whole time
I was just thinking things over.

1016
01:19:56,959 --> 01:20:00,545
I was, like... I was, like, meditating.

1017
01:20:03,549 --> 01:20:06,593
Then I sort of watched myself
from inside.

1018
01:20:08,762 --> 01:20:10,889
I realized it was ridiculous

1019
01:20:12,391 --> 01:20:16,478
being afraid, worrying about everything,

1020
01:20:16,562 --> 01:20:20,106
wishing I was dead. All that shit.
I'm tired of it.

1021
01:20:23,819 --> 01:20:25,737
It's the best day of my life.

1022
01:20:31,076 --> 01:20:33,244
I'm gonna miss you guys next year.

1023
01:20:42,421 --> 01:20:45,924
Cameron? Can I ask you a question?

1024
01:20:47,885 --> 01:20:49,052
Yeah.

1025
01:20:51,180 --> 01:20:54,265
Did you see me change out
of my clothes by the Jacuzzi?

1026
01:20:57,269 --> 01:20:58,269
Did you?

1027
01:21:00,773 --> 01:21:01,898
You saw me?

1028
01:21:02,566 --> 01:21:04,943
I thought you were catatonic.

1029
01:21:09,573 --> 01:21:11,115
That's okay.

1030
01:21:12,368 --> 01:21:13,868
I'm not embarrassed.

1031
01:21:16,330 --> 01:21:18,915
I better check on the car.

1032
01:21:32,596 --> 01:21:34,013
Hey, Ferris!

1033
01:21:35,724 --> 01:21:36,724
Yeah?

1034
01:21:39,895 --> 01:21:41,729
The miles aren't coming off.

1035
01:21:43,148 --> 01:21:45,817
The miles aren't coming off
going in reverse.

1036
01:21:52,741 --> 01:21:54,826
Well, I thought that might be a problem.

1037
01:21:54,910 --> 01:21:58,788
Just have to crack open the odometer,
roll it back by hand.

1038
01:22:00,207 --> 01:22:01,749
No. Forget it.

1039
01:22:03,794 --> 01:22:05,003
Forget it.

1040
01:22:11,010 --> 01:22:12,844
I gotta take a stand.

1041
01:22:17,516 --> 01:22:18,933
I'm bullshit.

1042
01:22:22,938 --> 01:22:25,189
I put up with everything.

1043
01:22:29,528 --> 01:22:32,238
My old man pushes me around.

1044
01:22:35,034 --> 01:22:37,201
I never say anything!

1045
01:22:42,041 --> 01:22:44,584
Well, he's not the problem.
I'm the problem.

1046
01:22:51,634 --> 01:22:53,259
I gotta take a stand.

1047
01:22:56,555 --> 01:22:58,931
I gotta take a stand against him.

1048
01:23:01,810 --> 01:23:04,604
I am not gonna sit on my ass

1049
01:23:05,189 --> 01:23:08,733
as the events that affect me unfold
to determine the course of my life.

1050
01:23:08,817 --> 01:23:10,443
I'm gonna take a stand.

1051
01:23:12,029 --> 01:23:13,863
I'm gonna defend it.

1052
01:23:15,240 --> 01:23:17,450
Right or wrong, I'm gonna defend it.

1053
01:23:29,588 --> 01:23:31,714
I'm so sick of his shit!

1054
01:23:32,716 --> 01:23:35,968
I can't stand him,
and I hate this goddamn car.

1055
01:23:36,053 --> 01:23:39,389
Who do you love? Who do you love?
You love a car.

1056
01:23:39,515 --> 01:23:42,016
You son of a bitch.

1057
01:24:05,040 --> 01:24:06,040
Shit.

1058
01:24:09,002 --> 01:24:10,837
I dented the shit out of it.

1059
01:24:15,718 --> 01:24:16,718
Good.

1060
01:24:20,889 --> 01:24:24,642
My father will come home,
he'll see what I did. I can't hide this.

1061
01:24:27,438 --> 01:24:31,023
He'll come home, he'll see what I did.
He'll have to deal with me.

1062
01:24:32,192 --> 01:24:34,110
I don't care, I really don't.

1063
01:24:35,904 --> 01:24:37,905
I'm just tired of being afraid.

1064
01:24:45,247 --> 01:24:46,497
Hell with him.

1065
01:24:50,419 --> 01:24:53,296
I can't wait to see the look
on the bastard's face.

1066
01:25:23,285 --> 01:25:24,535
What'd I do?

1067
01:25:35,798 --> 01:25:39,884
- What'd I do?
- You killed the car.

1068
01:26:18,090 --> 01:26:19,632
Whoa.

1069
01:26:22,094 --> 01:26:24,262
Holy shit.

1070
01:26:38,527 --> 01:26:40,111
Cameron, it's my fault.

1071
01:26:40,863 --> 01:26:41,946
I'll take the heat for it.

1072
01:26:42,030 --> 01:26:43,489
We'll wait for your father to come home

1073
01:26:43,574 --> 01:26:45,491
and when he gets here,
I'll tell him that I did it.

1074
01:26:45,576 --> 01:26:46,993
He hates me anyway.

1075
01:26:53,041 --> 01:26:55,501
No. I'll take it.

1076
01:26:56,044 --> 01:26:57,128
No, I'll take it.

1077
01:26:57,212 --> 01:27:00,047
No. No, you don't want this much heat.

1078
01:27:00,132 --> 01:27:01,674
I want it. If I didn't want it,

1079
01:27:01,758 --> 01:27:03,885
I wouldn't have let you
take the car out this morning.

1080
01:27:03,969 --> 01:27:06,262
I made you take the car this morning.

1081
01:27:06,346 --> 01:27:07,972
I could've stopped you.

1082
01:27:08,140 --> 01:27:11,183
It is possible to stop
Mr. Ferris Bueller, you know?

1083
01:27:11,268 --> 01:27:14,186
No, I want it. I'm gonna take it. That's it.

1084
01:27:15,314 --> 01:27:17,648
When Morris comes home,

1085
01:27:18,650 --> 01:27:20,943
he and I'll just have a little chat.

1086
01:27:22,821 --> 01:27:24,030
It's cool.

1087
01:27:24,865 --> 01:27:26,824
No, it's gonna be good.

1088
01:27:28,410 --> 01:27:29,911
Thanks anyway.

1089
01:27:39,004 --> 01:27:40,421
This is a shock to me.

1090
01:27:40,505 --> 01:27:43,090
I mean, first of all, I don't know
why she wasn't in school.

1091
01:27:43,175 --> 01:27:45,343
And second of all, I just can't believe

1092
01:27:45,427 --> 01:27:47,929
she came to you
with this story about an intruder.

1093
01:27:48,013 --> 01:27:52,099
Well, for whatever reason she did it,
I think she's had a pretty good scare.

1094
01:27:52,601 --> 01:27:55,102
Well, I really appreciate your calling me.
Really.

1095
01:27:55,187 --> 01:27:57,146
I can assure you that her father
and I are going

1096
01:27:57,230 --> 01:27:59,273
to have a long talk
with her when we get home.

1097
01:27:59,358 --> 01:28:00,733
Thank you so much.

1098
01:28:01,944 --> 01:28:04,779
Oh, by the way,
I hope your son is feeling better.

1099
01:28:04,947 --> 01:28:06,197
I beg your pardon?

1100
01:28:06,281 --> 01:28:09,200
Tell him all the guys
at the station here are pulling for him.

1101
01:28:10,202 --> 01:28:11,243
Oh, right.

1102
01:28:20,754 --> 01:28:23,214
- Hi.
- Don't "hi" me, young lady.

1103
01:28:23,715 --> 01:28:25,508
- I wanna get out of here, now, all right?
- Okay.

1104
01:28:25,592 --> 01:28:27,176
No, now. Let's get out of here.

1105
01:28:27,260 --> 01:28:28,928
- Okay.
- Okay?

1106
01:28:29,012 --> 01:28:30,012
- Yes.
- Now.

1107
01:28:30,097 --> 01:28:31,097
Fine.

1108
01:28:31,640 --> 01:28:32,640
Okay.

1109
01:28:37,771 --> 01:28:41,065
- She's a little hyper.
- Yeah.

1110
01:28:43,902 --> 01:28:48,072
Let's not ruin this
with a lot of talk, all right? Okay?

1111
01:28:49,366 --> 01:28:51,492
You didn't tell me your name.

1112
01:28:52,577 --> 01:28:57,331
Well, it's Jean,
but, a lot of guys call me Shauna.

1113
01:28:58,417 --> 01:28:59,750
Okay, Jean.

1114
01:29:00,335 --> 01:29:01,335
Cool.

1115
01:29:02,671 --> 01:29:04,088
That's great.

1116
01:29:05,173 --> 01:29:06,799
I'll see you, okay?

1117
01:29:08,010 --> 01:29:09,010
Yeah.

1118
01:29:12,264 --> 01:29:14,098
Jeanie, now!

1119
01:29:14,850 --> 01:29:18,227
- Now!
- Okay!

1120
01:29:26,153 --> 01:29:27,903
I had a great time today.

1121
01:29:28,822 --> 01:29:31,323
Yeah. It was pretty cool.

1122
01:29:33,785 --> 01:29:36,245
Do you...
Do you think Cameron's gonna be okay?

1123
01:29:36,329 --> 01:29:37,371
Oh, yeah.

1124
01:29:38,123 --> 01:29:40,624
Yeah, sure. For the first time in his life.

1125
01:29:40,917 --> 01:29:42,626
He's gonna be just fine.

1126
01:29:51,136 --> 01:29:54,472
You knew what you were doing when
you woke up this morning, didn't you?

1127
01:29:55,140 --> 01:29:57,641
Me? No.

1128
01:30:17,162 --> 01:30:20,915
Oh, shit. I have to go.

1129
01:30:22,959 --> 01:30:24,919
- I'll call you tonight.
- Okay.

1130
01:30:29,132 --> 01:30:31,675
- I love you!
- I love you, too!

1131
01:30:33,678 --> 01:30:35,346
He's gonna marry me.

1132
01:30:39,184 --> 01:30:41,811
Do you know what it's like
to be pulled out of work

1133
01:30:41,895 --> 01:30:44,313
to pick up your daughter
at the police station?

1134
01:30:44,397 --> 01:30:45,439
No, not really.

1135
01:30:45,524 --> 01:30:47,024
Well, on top of everything else,

1136
01:30:47,109 --> 01:30:50,486
I was about to close the damn deal
with the Vermont people.

1137
01:30:50,695 --> 01:30:52,113
I'm sorry.

1138
01:30:54,491 --> 01:30:57,368
I was gonna take my commission
and buy Ferris a car.

1139
01:30:59,246 --> 01:31:03,249
Jeanie, what the hell are you doing?
You trying to kill us?

1140
01:31:03,458 --> 01:31:04,959
God, look at this mess.

1141
01:31:05,043 --> 01:31:08,003
Paper all over the place.
I'll never get this back in order.

1142
01:31:15,929 --> 01:31:17,471
Jeanie!

1143
01:31:26,439 --> 01:31:30,025
- Slow down! Now! Now!
- I can't drive when you're yelling at me!

1144
01:31:30,193 --> 01:31:31,193
Stop it!

1145
01:32:01,975 --> 01:32:03,767
- Hi, how you doing? Ferris Bueller.
- Hi.

1146
01:33:32,023 --> 01:33:33,607
- No, don't get up.
- Hey.

1147
01:33:33,692 --> 01:33:35,192
Smells delicious.

1148
01:33:36,027 --> 01:33:37,611
- Dinner's ready.
- What?

1149
01:33:37,821 --> 01:33:39,196
Who's that?

1150
01:34:12,355 --> 01:34:15,858
- What's wrong?
- Everything.

1151
01:34:16,234 --> 01:34:18,861
I just picked up Jeanie
at the police station.

1152
01:34:20,905 --> 01:34:23,157
She got a speeding ticket,
another speeding ticket

1153
01:34:23,241 --> 01:34:25,034
and I lost the Vermont deal
because of her.

1154
01:34:25,118 --> 01:34:26,952
I think we should shoot her.

1155
01:34:33,752 --> 01:34:35,419
Looking for this?

1156
01:34:48,099 --> 01:34:49,475
I got you, Ferris.

1157
01:34:49,893 --> 01:34:52,102
- How's Ferris? Let's go check on him.
- Okay, honey. Yeah.

1158
01:34:52,979 --> 01:34:54,355
How was your day?

1159
01:34:55,398 --> 01:34:58,025
I have dreamed about this.

1160
01:34:59,110 --> 01:35:03,238
This time, goddamn, you little bastard,

1161
01:35:04,199 --> 01:35:06,408
I've got you right where I want you.

1162
01:35:06,659 --> 01:35:08,327
Ferris, we're home.

1163
01:35:10,580 --> 01:35:11,580
So,

1164
01:35:13,625 --> 01:35:17,044
how would you feel
about another year of high school?

1165
01:35:18,505 --> 01:35:22,299
Under my close personal supervision.

1166
01:35:24,052 --> 01:35:25,052
Hi.

1167
01:35:27,597 --> 01:35:31,475
Thank God you're all right. You know,
we've been worried sick about you.

1168
01:35:36,439 --> 01:35:38,899
Thank you, Mr. Rooney,
for driving him home.

1169
01:35:39,484 --> 01:35:43,612
Now I want you to go upstairs
and get in bed.

1170
01:35:54,791 --> 01:35:56,041
Scoot!

1171
01:35:57,669 --> 01:35:59,420
Can you imagine
someone as sick as Ferris

1172
01:35:59,504 --> 01:36:01,797
trying to walk home from the hospital?

1173
01:36:03,299 --> 01:36:04,758
Oh, kids.

1174
01:36:07,887 --> 01:36:11,890
By the way, Mr. Rooney,
you left your wallet on the kitchen floor.

1175
01:37:18,082 --> 01:37:19,082
Honey.

1176
01:37:20,752 --> 01:37:23,754
- He's still awfully warm.
- How do you feel?

1177
01:37:25,089 --> 01:37:28,258
150% better. Thank you.

1178
01:37:30,094 --> 01:37:31,094
Please,

1179
01:37:31,304 --> 01:37:34,765
don't make me stay home again.
I wanna go to school.

1180
01:37:35,517 --> 01:37:39,770
I have to graduate in June. And I want...

1181
01:37:40,355 --> 01:37:41,813
Ferris, you're sick.

1182
01:37:42,315 --> 01:37:44,858
Now don't go pushing it
and making yourself worse.

1183
01:37:45,985 --> 01:37:48,779
- Maybe you're right, Dad.
- I know I'm right, pal.

1184
01:37:50,657 --> 01:37:52,950
How'd you get to be so sweet?

1185
01:37:53,409 --> 01:37:55,619
Years of practice.

1186
01:38:05,964 --> 01:38:07,130
Blanket.

1187
01:38:17,642 --> 01:38:18,642
Get well.

1188
01:38:20,311 --> 01:38:21,728
Come on.

1189
01:38:24,482 --> 01:38:28,652
Listen, I'm going to get myself settled
and I'll bring a hot cup of soup, okay?

1190
01:38:39,330 --> 01:38:40,330
Yup.

1191
01:38:40,873 --> 01:38:43,166
I said it before and I'll say it again.

1192
01:38:43,668 --> 01:38:45,460
Life moves pretty fast.

1193
01:38:45,878 --> 01:38:49,590
If you don't stop and look around
once in a while, you could miss it.

1194
01:39:00,685 --> 01:39:03,312
Four years of chasing this kid.

1195
01:39:04,147 --> 01:39:07,524
Four years he has been
making a fool of me.

1196
01:39:18,036 --> 01:39:21,872
Hey, Mr. Rooney, what's going on?

1197
01:39:24,709 --> 01:39:27,044
Did you get in a fight?

1198
01:39:28,504 --> 01:39:29,713
Want a lift?

1199
01:41:15,820 --> 01:41:19,322
I bet you never smelled
a real school bus before.

1200
01:41:33,296 --> 01:41:34,421
Gummy Bear?

1201
01:41:36,048 --> 01:41:39,259
They've been in my pocket.
They're real warm and soft.

1202
01:42:27,266 --> 01:42:28,767
You're still here?

1203
01:42:31,604 --> 01:42:32,813
It's over.

1204
01:42:34,857 --> 01:42:36,024
Go home.

1205
01:42:40,530 --> 01:42:42,000
Go.
